      "term" : "obstruction of the ureter or renal calyx",
      "definition" : "means a mechanical blockage of\nurinary drainage due to an endogenous or exogenous pathological structure or\nextraneous material that compresses, occludes, displaces or infiltrates the renal\npelvicalyceal system or ureter. This definition includes obstruction from:\n(a) aneurysm of the aorta, iliac artery, renal artery or uterine artery;\n(b) ascites;\n(c) benign or malignant neoplasm of the kidney, renal pelvis, ureter,\nbladder, uterus, ovary, prostate, colon or rectum;\n(d) blunt or penetrating traumatic injury of the affected region;\n(e) collagen vascular disease;\n(f) endometriosis;\n(g) faecal impaction;\n(h) fungus bezoar of the urinary tract (Candida albicans, Candida\ntropicalis, Aspergillus);\n(i) genitourinary tuberculosis;\n(j) Hodgkin's lymphoma;\n(k) indwelling ureteric stent;\n(l) inflammatory bowel disease;\n(m) migrated intrauterine contraceptive device;\n(n) non-Hodgkin's lymphoma;\n(o) ovarian hyperstimulation;\n(p) pancreatitis;\n(q) pelvic actinomycosis;\n(r) pelvic inflammatory disease;\n(s) pelvic or abdominal abscess;\n(t) pelvic or abdominal amyloidoma;\n(u) pelvic or abdominal haematoma;\n(v) renal arachnoid cyst;\n(w) renal hydatid cyst;\n(x) renal stone;\n(y) retroperitoneal fibrosis;\n(z) schistosomiasis;\n(aa) sloughed renal papilla;\n(bb) sub-ureteral collagen injection;\n(cc) surgical ligation of the ureter;\n(dd) ureteral herniation;\n(ee) ureteral polyp;\n(ff) ureteric stricture;\n(gg) ureteritis; or\n(hh) uterine prolapse"
